New ICEJ offices open in Central African Republic, Cameroon 🇨🇫 
.
This past weekend, Dr. Mojmir Kallus, the ICEJ’s Vice President for International Affairs, began an extended visit to Africa, beginning with an interdenominational conference on Israel in Bangui, Central African Republic.
.
The three-day gathering was attended by senior church leaders, the Mayor of Bangui, and hundreds of enthusiastic believers. It concluded with the installation of Firmin Ngatoua as national director of our new office for ICEJ-Central African Republic. Mojmir will now continue on to Cameroon for another Israel conference and the opening of our new representation there headed by Apostle Julius Ekie. The ministry trip will finish in Gabon, where our national director and central African regional coordinator, Judicael Monguengui, will host his second annual Israel conference for church leaders from throughout the region and continent.

Reposted from @impactyouth412 Nothing you do today will be more important than spending quality alone time with God.  Read your Bible and pray every day.  Make it your top priority. It will make you more like Jesus which is always needed in everyone’s life. 

After giving us a like, comment, and a follow, grab your Bible and read it for a little while.  Even reading just a few verses is better than nothing. 

I recommend you start in the book of John.  It’s easy to understand and it will help you learn more about Jesus.  After a few weeks, you’ll develop the habit of reading your Bible daily and you’ll wonder why you didn’t start sooner.

시146:4 그의 호흡이 끊어지면 흙으로 돌아가서 그 날에 그이 생각이 소멸하리로다
시146:5 야곱의 하나님을 자기의 도움으로 삼으며 여호와 자기 하나님에게 자기의 소망을 두는 자는 복이 있도다
시146:6 여호와는 천지와 바다와 그 중의 만물을 지으시며 영원히 진실함을 지키시며 
시146:7 억눌린 사람들을 위해 정의로 심판하시며 주린 자들에게 먹을 것을 주시는 이시로다 여호와께서는 갇힌 자들에게 자유를 주시는도다 
시146:8 여호와께서 맹인들의 눈을 여시며 여호와께서 비굴한 자들을 일으키시며 여호와께서 의인들을 사랑하시며 
시146:9 여호와께서 나그네들을 보호하시며 고아와 과부를 붙드시고 악인들의 길은 굽게 하시는도다 
시146:10 시온아 여호와는 영원히 다스리시고 네 하나님은 대대로 통치하시리로다 할렐루야

《Tuo padre e io, angosciati, ti cercavamo.》

📖 Dal Vangelo secondo Luca
Lc 2,41-51

I genitori di Gesù si recavano ogni anno a Gerusalemme per la festa di Pasqua. Quando egli ebbe dodici anni, vi salirono secondo la consuetudine della festa. Ma, trascorsi i giorni, mentre riprendevano la via del ritorno, il fanciullo Gesù rimase a Gerusalemme, senza che i genitori se ne accorgessero. Credendo che egli fosse nella comitiva, fecero una giornata di viaggio, e poi si misero a cercarlo tra i parenti e i conoscenti; non avendolo trovato, tornarono in cerca di lui a Gerusalemme.
Dopo tre giorni lo trovarono nel tempio, seduto in mezzo ai maestri, mentre li ascoltava e li interrogava. E tutti quelli che l'udivano erano pieni di stupore per la sua intelligenza e le sue risposte.
Al vederlo restarono stupiti, e sua madre gli disse: «Figlio, perché ci hai fatto questo? Ecco, tuo padre e io, angosciati, ti cercavamo». Ed egli rispose loro: «Perché mi cercavate? Non sapevate che io devo occuparmi delle cose del Padre mio?». Ma essi non compresero ciò che aveva detto loro.
Scese dunque con loro e venne a Nàzaret e stava loro sottomesso. Sua madre custodiva tutte queste cose nel suo cuore.

Parola del Signore 🙏🏻

VICTORY👏🏽

Deuteronomy 20:4 - ‘For the Lord your God is the one who goes with you to fight for you against your enemies to give you victory’.

Victory is ours through faith as long as we abide in Jesus. Our victory comes because God is with us. In fact, victory is a part of our inheritance and identity in Christ because we are ‘more than conquerors through him who loved us’. It’s easy to rely on your strength to get what you want in life. But with God you will always be victorious. But when praying for victory, don’t forget its God that makes it possible!

6月25日(土)　放蕩息子のお兄さん

おまえはいつも私といっしょにいる。
 私のものは、全部おまえのものだ。

　　　　  ルカの福音書15章31節
 

聖書の中には、有名な放蕩息子のお話があります。

ところで、その放蕩息子にはお兄さんがいました。
彼はとても忠実に勤勉に働きお父さんに仕えていました。

そのお兄さんが、
畑仕事から帰って来て家に近づくと、
音楽や踊りの音が聞こえて来ました。

それで、しもべのひとりを呼んで、
これはいったい何事かと尋ねると
『弟さんがお帰りになったのです。
　無事な姿をお迎えしたというので、
　おとうさんが、肥えた子牛をほふらせなさったのです。』
という答えを聞いて、兄はおこって、
家にはいろうともしませんでした。

それで、父が出て来て、
いろいろなだめてみましたが、
兄は父にこう言ったのです。
『ご覧なさい。
　長年の間、私はおとうさんに仕え、
　戒めを破ったことは一度もありません。
　その私には、友だちと楽しめと言って、
　子山羊一匹下さったことがありません。
　それなのに、遊女におぼれて
　あなたの身代を食いつぶして帰って来た
　このあなたの息子のためには、
　肥えた子牛をほふらせなさったのですか。』

お兄さんにしてみれば、
やりきれなかったのでしょう。
わかる気はします。

しかし父は彼に、こう言いました。
『おまえはいつも私といっしょにいる。
　私のものは、全部おまえのものだ。
　だがおまえの弟は、
　死んでいたのが生き返って来たのだ。
　いなくなっていたのが見つかったのだから、
　楽しんで喜ぶのは当然ではないか。』

もしお兄さんが帰ってきて、
お父さんと一緒に弟を抱きしめて、
喜べたらどんなに素晴らしかったでしょう。
そしてお兄さんも幸せだったと思います。

どうして、それが出来なかったのでしょう。

お兄さんは、お父さんに仕えていました。
でも、愛と恵みの関係、
つまり信頼、信仰の関わりではなく、
律法的になっていたのだと思います。

またお父さんが
兄の誕生日に子牛を屠ろうとしても
「いいよ、もったいないから
　そんなことしなくてもいい」
と言ったのかもしれません。

お父さんに
素直に大胆に求めたり願ったりする
関係ではなくなっていたのでしょう。

だから、
弟が放蕩三昧して帰ってきた時、
お父さんが肥えた子牛を屠って
お祝いしていたのが許せなかったのです。

私たちも気をつけないといけません。
最初は弟のように
救われて喜んで奉仕しているのですが、
年月をへてくると
お兄さんのようになってしまいやすいのです。

信仰と信頼を持って、
愛と恵みに満ちておられる父なる神さまに
仕えて行きましよう。

イエス・キリストはあなたを愛しておられます。

聖書ってこんなにおもしろい」

In that day you will ask in My name, and I do not say to you that I shall pray the Father for you; John 16:26

Until a person sees the revelation in these words of Jesus in our theme verse, one wouldn't really see the importance of personally relating with God, or communicating with Him directly.

Jesus talking to His disciples said, "until now you have asked nothing in my name, ask and you will receive that your joy may be full". Then He said, "in that day, you will ask in my name, And I do not say to you that I shall pray the Father for you,

"for the Father Himself loves you"! What clearer terms could there possibly be, to emphasise the importance of you, developing your own personal walk with God?

If Jesus Himself said, listen, I'm not saying I'll pray for you to the Father, then why depend on a pastor or your mum, or one Saint or the other? No! He wants you to approach Him personally. And why? Because the Father Himself loves you, as He loves Jesus His Son also.

Prayer: Father I thank you for your love for me, I praise you Lord for granting me direct access to you, for making me your son also, through Jesus the first born. I chose to practice relating with you personally, and not through a third party. In Jesus name I pray. Amen

Jesus said in everything we do we should look to do it for God’s Kingdom. For example, doing good to everyone around us so they can see God’s light in our lives and through this turn to Him by accepting Jesus as their Saviour. 

Jesus goes on to say we should equally seek God’s righteousness which will guide us in how we can also live righteous lives.

When we live our lives this way we are living according to the will of God for us. Matthew 7:21 says only the people who do God’s will will see God’s Kingdom and moreover Matthew 6:33 says when we seek God first we will receive all that we need.

Daily Devotion - Ecclesiastes #5

Ecclesiastes 1 - The Vanity of Life

1 The words of the Preacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem.

2 “Vanity of vanities,” says the Preacher;
“Vanity of vanities, all is vanity.”

3 What profit has a man from all his labor
In which he toils under the sun?
4 One generation passes away, and another generation comes;
But the earth abides forever.
5 The sun also rises, and the sun goes down,
And [c]hastens to the place where it arose.
6 The wind goes toward the south,
And turns around to the north;
The wind whirls about continually,
And comes again on its circuit.
7 All the rivers run into the sea,
Yet the sea is not full;
To the place from which the rivers come,
There they return again.
8 All things are full of labor;
Man cannot express it.
The eye is not satisfied with seeing,
Nor the ear filled with hearing.

9 That which has been is what will be,
That which is done is what will be done,
And there is nothing new under the sun.
10 Is there anything of which it may be said,
“See, this is new”?
It has already been in ancient times before us.
11 There is no remembrance of former things,
Nor will there be any remembrance of things that are to come
By those who will come after.

The Grief of Wisdom
12 I, the Preacher, was king over Israel in Jerusalem. 13 And I set my heart to seek and search out by wisdom concerning all that is done under heaven; this burdensome task God has given to the sons of man, by which they may be exercised. 14 I have seen all the works that are done under the sun; and indeed, all is vanity and grasping for the wind.

15 What is crooked cannot be made straight,
And what is lacking cannot be numbered.

16 I communed with my heart, saying, “Look, I have attained greatness, and have gained more wisdom than all who were before me in Jerusalem. My heart has understood great wisdom and knowledge.” 17 And I set my heart to know wisdom and to know madness and folly. I perceived that this also is grasping for the wind.

18 For in much wisdom is much grief,
And he who increases knowledge increases sorrow.

OPEN DOORS // Wat als je voor Jezus hebt gekozen, maar mensen om je heen vinden dat niks en worden hier heel boos om? Hoe kun je daar dan mee omgaan? Het overkwam Timóteo uit Colombia.

De familie van Timóteo hoorde bij een animistische stam. Het animisme is een vorm van geloven waarbij niet God, maar bijvoorbeeld overleden voorouders en dieren worden vereerd. Maar het gezin van Timóteo kwam in contact met het christelijk geloof. Dit vonden hun stamgenoten niet leuk: ze waren bang dat de geesten boos zouden worden.

Lees de hele blog via onze link in bio of via de link in de story

Wist je dat er wereldwijd meer dan 360 (!) miljoen christenen vervolgd worden? Dit betekent dat ze buitengesloten, gevangengezet of mishandeld worden om hun geloof. De organisatie Open Doors komt voor deze christenen op, bijvoorbeeld door Bijbels uit te delen, noodhulp te geven of door christenen te leren hoe ze kunnen omgaan met vervolging.

I am #ProChoice!!!

Being a young Christian girl, I am empowered to believe that I am protected, that if I make the right choices, bad things won't happen... Unfortunately that is not at all what the Bible tells us... God warns us, tells us and intercedes on our behalf because of the attacks that WILL COME. I am blessed to say that I have never been in a place where I have been s3xually abused, rap3d, mol3st3d or in any away us3d for another's pleasure... I have never been in a position where I was forced to marry as a kid, or even carry another child while still being one myself... I was never in a position where I had to choose between my life or another... THEREFORE I HAVE NO RIGHT TO MAKE THIS CHOICE FOR ANYONE ELSE !!! 
I am however in a position of empathy and understanding. I am in a place where I can take a stand, this might not mean that I would be able to change anything, but if it could open your mind, or even make you feel that you're not alone, I am even more blessed. 
To the families, girls and women who are dealing with the judgement, pressure and hatred... I apologize!
To the women who endure, forgive and love, I honor and to those who were not "strong" enough, I respect...
God tells us to love, to forgive and to live our life in seek of His Kingdom, to be obedient and not to judge others, but to rather take a look in the mirror. 
I DON'T KNOW YOUR WHY, but I know WHO we can all turn to. I pray that God protects us, that He guides us, for as he says we are foolish... There is no "winners" to what is going on...

And if I affended you, take it up with the person looking back in that bathroom mirror..

If you agree, share and leave a comment!

Esta ilustración de La Biblia, publicada por @smespana y @ppc.editorial muestra una escena de la vida cotidiana en una calle de Jerusalén en tiempos de Jesús y servía como base para mostrar las virtudes cristianas, que al fin y al cabo son las humanas.
El cristianismo considera las teologales: fe, esperaranza y caridad; y las cardinales: prudencia, fortaleza, justicia y templanza.

¿Alguien podría estar en desacuerdo con ellas? Seguramente no si vinieran de una corriente guachi de un país exótico. Pero el cristianismo huele un poquito a naftalina...

Hay otra virtud más ignorada popularmente: la generosidad, que es una virtud propiciatoria, constructiva.... pero profundamente anticapitalista y revolucionaria.

Le dedico este post con mucho cariño a @crisgutiamigo una persona que reune y transmite todas estas virtudes para el bien del mundo.

Yesterday I was playing with my grandson and every time my son would disappear around the corner in my house Kingston couldn’t see him and thought he was left and started getting sad because his daddy was gone. But was he really? My son would pop around the corner and that big ole smile would return immediately along with his big laugh. Oh there you are daddy, and everything was ok again in the little guys world. He was sure he had left until he saw his dad peak around the corner. Some of us can be that way with God at times can’t we? We think he has left us alone sometimes and then he peaks around the corner or we hear his voice or he taps us on the heart and we are ok again. But you have got to know that he will never leave you or forsake you and just because you feel like you can’t see him and this time you know that you have done it by not staying close enough to him and he has finally left you to fin for yourself. He then peaks around the corner of your life smiles and you know everything is about to get good because he is there for you to lean on again. Do you feel like you are alone? Or you are left to figure this problem out on your own. Don’t look now but your daddy is about to peak around the corner of your life and bring you back to a state of bliss because he’s got a big old smile on his face as he says, “here I am, I love you son. I love you so much buddy“. Peace settles in and you give way to joy and life is good because daddy is in the house. 
Live Love and Let Love Make it a Great Life!!!!
Shane

DIRECT ACCESS

In that day you will ask in My name, and I do not say to you that I shall pray the Father for you; John 16:26

Until a person sees the revelation in these words of Jesus in our theme verse, one wouldn't really see the importance of personally relating with God, or communicating with Him directly. 

Jesus talking to His disciples said, "until now you have asked nothing in my name, ask and you will receive that your joy may be full". Then He said, "in that day, you will ask in my name, And I do not say to you that I shall pray the Father for you, 

"for the Father Himself loves you"! What clearer terms could there possibly be, to emphasise the importance of you, developing your own personal walk with God?

If Jesus Himself said, listen, I'm not saying I'll pray for you to the Father, then why depend on a pastor or your mum, or one Saint or the other? No! He wants you to approach Him personally. And why? Because the Father Himself loves you, as He loves Jesus His Son also.

Prayer: Father I thank you for your love for me, I praise you Lord for granting me direct access to you, for making me your son also, through Jesus the first born. I chose to practice relating with you personally, and not through a third party. In Jesus name I pray. Amen

Be thankful in all circumstances, for this is God’s will for you who belong to Christ Jesus. 1 Thessalonians 5:18
______

You may be asking yourself, why should I be thankful in times when life is draining, When the sky looks bleak, and it feels as if hope is an illusion.?

Whatever it may be, God's will for you and me is to be thankful in all circumstances. Our lives are not our own. We live it for God, and He knows exactly what He is doing during the seasons of our lives. 

It may feel as if you stand alone. It may feel as if there is no way out. But this season, regardless of how we feel or how things may seem, "trust in the Lord with all your heart and never lean on your understanding, but in your ways acknowledge Him, and He will direct you on a straight path."

Yes, it is hard to do, and yes, it is not fair, but one thing I know is that no one who places their confidence in Christ ever comes out disappointed. 

You have to hold on to the God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob and know that there is no season in your life that He is unaware of. 

Your help does not come from the mountains or anywhere else. It comes from God who made heaven and earth. He will not let you stumble. Our God is not a God who slumbers nor sleeps. He watches over all His Children and stands with them as a protective shade. He Will does not allow the sun to harm you in the daytime or the mood at night time (psalm 121:1-8). 

As long as you stick to the will of God for your life, your story ends well. ✨️✨️

Myths about Theology of the Body

Myth: Theology of the Body is about following the rules of the faith; the letter of the law.

Reality: Theology of the Body is not legalism, it is a look at the way we are called to live. Jesus is after our hearts. His words are not so much a condemnation of our hearts, but a calling out to it.

Myth: We should repress our temptation and desires and avoid sinful thoughts outright.

Reality: Repressing our desires and avoiding our sin does not move us closer to God. We need to open up our longings to God, become vulnerable, and shift our hearts and the way we think back towards the Lord.

Myth: Theology of the body is only about sex and sexuality.

Reality: Yes, TOB talks about sex and sexuality. However, it is much richer than just that conversation. It is about love and our expression of love through the gift of our bodies.

Myth: God is tyrannical, and will strike down sinners.

Reality: God is infinitely compassionate. In the moments when we call God, He humbles himself by desending down to be with us. His love never wavers, no matter the actions of man.

Here are some quotes and ideas that have stuck us this week:

Indulgence and repression are not the only options and they fail to recognize the true beauty of God’s gifts. 

Theology of the Body seeks to remind us that we are created for infinity, but at times we seek the infinite in finite things. Or we try to to repress these very desires. 

A big chunk of the Christian life we are called towards is undoing the the lies we believe about God day in and day out.

God is not a tyrant. But He doesn’t want us grasping at sin and He hates sin because it hurts us. 

We’re created for infinity, but as “finites” we can’t access it in this life. This places us in a radical posture of dependence on the “Infinite One” to grant us the gift of Himself. 

Our thirst can only be satisfied in Him. 

Do you believe that is true?

When praying becomes a habit, success becomes a lifestyle!

Amberwood is a new release from @clivechristianperfume and it’s taken me a few wearings to get my head round it. It starts quite spicy - peppery and aromatic - I want a word that sort of conveys that it has an airiness to it. Er. So maybe airy. Yes. Airy. It’s very smooth and has a luxurious vibe from the ambroxan or whatever else it is that’s rounding out all the rougher edges and making it all nice. As it develops it smells a little like an unsweetened vanilla ice cream. The creaminess of the musks keeping it all very lovely. The fragrance seems to vanish and then return here and there. It lasts a very long time but sometimes I can’t smell it at all. 
 
Overall I think I like this a lot. Potentially it could even be a love. It’s certainly much more involved than initially it first seemed and that’s in keeping with the high quality nature of the house.

"Tuo padre e io, angosciati, ti cercavamo."

Signore Gesù guariscici.

•Dal Vangelo secondo Luca (Lc 2,41-51)
I genitori di Gesù si recavano ogni anno a Gerusalemme per la festa di Pasqua. Quando egli ebbe dodici anni, vi salirono secondo la consuetudine della festa. Ma, trascorsi i giorni, mentre riprendevano la via del ritorno, il fanciullo Gesù rimase a Gerusalemme, senza che i genitori se ne accorgessero. Credendo che egli fosse nella comitiva, fecero una giornata di viaggio, e poi si misero a cercarlo tra i parenti e i conoscenti; non avendolo trovato, tornarono in cerca di lui a Gerusalemme.
Dopo tre giorni lo trovarono nel tempio, seduto in mezzo ai maestri, mentre li ascoltava e li interrogava. E tutti quelli che l'udivano erano pieni di stupore per la sua intelligenza e le sue risposte.
Al vederlo restarono stupiti, e sua madre gli disse: «Figlio, perché ci hai fatto questo? Ecco, tuo padre e io, angosciati, ti cercavamo». Ed egli rispose loro: «Perché mi cercavate? Non sapevate che io devo occuparmi delle cose del Padre mio?». Ma essi non compresero ciò che aveva detto loro.
Scese dunque con loro e venne a Nàzaret e stava loro sottomesso. Sua madre custodiva tutte queste cose nel suo cuore.

+ Dal Vangelo secondo Luca (Lc 2,41-51)

I genitori di Gesù si recavano ogni anno a Gerusalemme per la festa di Pasqua. Quando egli ebbe dodici anni, vi salirono secondo la consuetudine della festa. Ma, trascorsi i giorni, mentre riprendevano la via del ritorno, il fanciullo Gesù rimase a Gerusalemme, senza che i genitori se ne accorgessero. Credendo che egli fosse nella comitiva, fecero una giornata di viaggio, e poi si misero a cercarlo tra i parenti e i conoscenti; non avendolo trovato, tornarono in cerca di lui a Gerusalemme. 
Dopo tre giorni lo trovarono nel tempio, seduto in mezzo ai maestri, mentre li ascoltava e li interrogava. E tutti quelli che l’udivano erano pieni di stupore per la sua intelligenza e le sue risposte. 
Al vederlo restarono stupiti, e sua madre gli disse: «Figlio, perché ci hai fatto questo? Ecco, tuo padre e io, angosciati, ti cercavamo». Ed egli rispose loro: «Perché mi cercavate? Non sapevate che io devo occuparmi delle cose del Padre mio?». Ma essi non compresero ciò che aveva detto loro. 
Scese dunque con loro e venne a Nàzaret e stava loro sottomesso. Sua madre custodiva tutte queste cose nel suo cuore. 

Parola del Signore

Jeremiah and Mark spent a meaningful evening with some young men from Gugulethu township sharing testimonies and life experiences with one another. 
These young men have unbelievable challenges growing up amidst extreme poverty, drugs, and gangsterism. Add to that the persecution and loneliness that comes from standing alone amongst peers for serving Christ. They are also at odds with their own culture steeped in ancestral worship making their decision to serve Jesus Christ even harder. 
Please pray for this budding young peoples group at Center of Hope church in Gugs and our dear family Pastors Vuyo and Lydia his wife for leading the charge in spending invaluable time with these men and women mentoring them in Christ 🙌🏼

When the Mughal power in North India was passing through its last phase.  So a storm arose in India, that was the storm of change, two types of groups were formed in North India, one was those who wanted to live on the basis of old memories, secondly those who wanted change, the British showed their influence and made this change.  In order to carry forward the concept of  These buildings would have fulfilled the needs of the British and at the same time would have left the impression that the mixed culture of North India, our customs, our education system have become old.  If we can move forward then we have to adopt western culture and start with the education system there.  And this was the reason that people started going to Europe for education at that time, and the British also sent their children to London to study.  But the British were very smart and think ahead.  They had already thought that if something untoward happens to us, then our children should be present for the responsibility.  And we all know this thing that they never used to employ Indians on good posts. For example, the Church Missionary Society of England established St. John's College, Agra in 1850.  Although these educational institutions were built by the British for their needs, but these educational institutions contributed a lot in the formation of independent India.  There is a long list of those who have taken education from here, who have served in high positions in independent India.  Including the ninth President of India, Shankar Dayal Sharma.

Hi I’m Stephanie and I’m a recovering addict of American Christianity. 
My addiction has caused me to ruin relationships in the past with judgment, exclusion, and self-righteousness. (I still have the ability to ruin relationships with these things but it’s not because “my faith” encourages those things, they are just character flaws.)
My addiction to American Christianity has caused me to doubt reality, to look for mystical causes to things that have blatant physical and scientific explanations. It led me to “pray the pain away” rather than get the appropriate help needed. 
My addiction has caused me to “love the sinner but hate the sin” a covert way to say my love and God’s love is conditional based on what I believe is morally correct. 
It led me to believe violence and killing is the appropriate response to other kinds of violence. 
It has led me to hate myself, my gender, and my sexuality. It has caused me to hide parts of who I am for fear of being judged, excluded, or shunned. 
My addiction to American Christianity led me to be emotionally and spiritually abused again and again until I developed complex PTSD.
My addiction to American Christianity led me to spiritually abuse others with my moralistic and black and white teachings as a youth worker/pastor. 
My addiction, which initially seemed to save me and bring me in to belonging and care, slowly and corrosively led to my near ruin and death. 
American Christianity is a drug that almost killed me and has killed so many to drugs, alcohol, mental illness, and physical manifestations of its trauma. 
American Christianity keeps giving out its cheap drug of control and bringing hell to earth rather than heaven. It is deplorable and I hate it for the drug that it is and the damage it continues to wreck havoc in my life, the lives people that I love, the vulnerable among us, and all of America.

Can't get over it's beauty 😍🥺.

I used to see these beautiful monuments in my history books and often get amused. I used to keep staring them for hours, often thinking will I ever get to see even any one monument from all of these listed in my book.

Coming from a small town, things which might be usual for many people are often a dream come true for me.
 
When finally I get the chance to see these monuments through my naked eyes, at first I don't believe it. But then again when I come back to my senses, I feel nothing but grateful. I feel alive. 💕

When I visited Lotus temple, there were so many feeling going inside me. Beneath all these feelings one was of happiness, happiness  to see people of all religious background coming there and sitting and talking and everyone was in aww of it's beauty.

It was such a secular place, anyone can go inside and read their religious books, in silence. Can you just imagine Hindu's, Muslim's, Sikh's, Christian's all coming at one place without any  hatred.

Now that's what secular India is 💕.
